<ResourceDictionary xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
                    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml">

    <!--
        DELIBERATELY EMPTY.

        Earlier this file merged a palette so brushes were resolvable at
        parse time. Now every brush reference in the codebase uses
        {DynamicResource ...} (deferred resolution), and ThemeManager
        installs the active palette directly into Application.Resources
        at startup as the SOLE source of brush instances.

        Keeping this file empty (rather than deleting it) lets all the
        control dictionaries keep their existing merge of Brushes.xaml
        without churning every file. Brush hot-swap works because there's
        no shadowed copy in a nested merge to keep consumers stuck on the
        old palette.
    -->

</ResourceDictionary>
